      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I see a better way: just <code>LocalDate.parse(rawDate)</code> ! <code>String.format</code> is being used in a total wrong form here, actually just returning the first string; the <code>DateTimeFormatter</code> is not being used at all; <code>parse</code> is a <code>static</code> method of <code>LocalDate</code>;  <code>formattedDate</code> is <b>not</b> a formatted date, not even a <code>String</code> (as requested in question)"
